		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><persName role="author">J. ABRAHAM</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p>Attorney and <sic>Counsellor</sic> at Law&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">AND</p>
				<p>Solicitor in Chancery.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>&#44; <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#47;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I enclose &#36;5 which you will please<lb/> credit me with.  I cannot omit the opportunity<lb/> to express my humble approbation of your course with<lb/> respect to the wise Dr I trust you receive more satis<lb/>&#45;factory assurances of the confidence reposed in you by<lb/> all the community.  I coincide precisely with your<lb/> views which if I understand them correctly&#44; are&#44; that<lb/> many improvements may be made in our forms by a<lb/> <hi rend="underline">duly</hi> &#38; <hi rend="underline">properly constituted</hi> body&#44; but for any man to<lb/> lop off here&#44; another there&#44; and a thin elsewhere&#44; there<lb/> can be no limit &#38; the tree would eventually be left not<lb/> only without fruit but void of branches &#38; finally<lb/> the trunk &#38; root would disappear&#59; combat such result<lb/> you do your duty only&#44; go on with the good work<lb/> you will finally reap the reward.  I wish<lb/> you to insert in your cover the card I annex &#38; let<lb/> me know what it will cost pr annum</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Joseph Abraham</persName></p>
				<p>&#40;Over&#41;</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Edr Occident</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><del><placeName>New York</placeName></del></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
		</body>
